From the NEW album "FLO Chill 3: LoFi Jazz", this song "Chill of the Night" is our expression of the FLO (For the Love Of) way of life. Some of our best memories are created in the chill of the night. Sustaining a foundation of trust and friendship is all about keeping communication strong and giving your best energy to those most important in your life while making memories with them in meaningful ways.  No matter where you are in life, live it with a positive bounce and FLO.

Marcus Johnson is an independent Billboard top 10 jazz pianist, NAACP Image Award nominee, owner of FLO Brands and FLO Wine, JD & MBA, philanthropist & father. 

Matthew Shell is an acclaimed, GRAMMY.com featured guitarist, engineer, & producer (Arun Shenoy, Masa Takumi, Kenny McNeil, Selena Gomez, Gerald Albright, Paul Jackson Jr., Greg Adams, Philip Lawrence, O.A.R., & Lana Lubany, among others).

This song also features saxophone, flute, mixing, and mastering by Douglas Lira as well as co-production and engineering by Erik Fredriksen.
